Governor Nyesom Wike of Rivers State has appointed new set of Commissioners and other state officials, reconstituting the state cabinet, after dissolving the state exco two weeks ago.
Some of the new commissioners include Professor Zaccheaus Adangor (SAN), reappointed the Attorney General and Commissioner for Justice; Isaac Kamalu, reappointed Commissioner for Finance; Alabo George-Kelly appointed Commissioner for the Ministry of Works, also supervising his former office on Special Project, etc.
The commissioners were sworn in on Friday by the governor.
